<p dir="auto">Context Mode uses <a href="https://github.com/WiseLibs/better-sqlite3">better-sqlite3</a> on Node.js, which ships prebuilt native binaries for most platforms. On glibc &gt;= 2.31 systems (Ubuntu 20.04+, Debian 11+, Fedora 34+, macOS, Windows), <code>npm install</code> works without any build tools.</p>
<p dir="auto"><strong>Linux + Node.js &gt;= 22.13:</strong> Context Mode automatically uses the built-in <code>node:sqlite</code> module instead of <code>better-sqlite3</code>. This eliminates the native addon entirely, avoiding <a href="https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/62515" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/nodejs/node/issues/62515/hovercard">sporadic SIGSEGV crashes</a> caused by V8's <code>madvise(MADV_DONTNEED)</code> corrupting the addon's <code>.got.plt</code> section on Linux. No configuration needed — detection is automatic. Falls back to <code>better-sqlite3</code> on older Node.js versions.</p>
